<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>There is currently no way to force a connection to close in Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract.  The implicit way is to destroy the adapter object, but in some cases this is not effective in closing the connection to the database.</p>

<p>For instance, in the case of the Zend_Db unit tests, connections accumulate until they exceed the capacity of the RDBMS server.</p>

<p>Please implement a closeConnection() abstract method in Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract.  Call this method in the tearDown() method of the unit tests.  Users can also use this to manage connections more explicitly, though most often it is not necessary.</p>

